festival.introText:
Live At Leeds is a metropolitan music festival held annually across a variety of venues in Leeds. The ethos has always been to celebrate the best in upcoming local talent alongside more established national and international artists. Over the past eight years, the likes of Mumford & Sons, Ed Sheeran, The Maccabees, London Grammar, Alt J and Jake Bugg have graced their stages.

The main event hosts over 100 bands playing across a range of venues around Leeds, all of which are accessible via the purchase of a Live at Leeds festival wristband.

faqs.question: Where is Live At Leeds in the Park?
faqs.answer: Live At Leeds in the Park is located at Temple Newsam in Leeds.
